{"source_key":"sha256-3853b3aef295de2a187e47a8e3f58ad2","record_index":21,"record_hash":"sha256:2924e9787d07a4ef05a33a8da2b36d038ac36e210ad34b57403a1703e7e9618e","timestamp":"2026-05-15T18:32:38.767Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yes, but normal `git log` won’t see truly unreferenced commits.\n\nFirst try reflogs, because most “lost” commits are still there:\n\n```bash\ngit reflog --date=iso --all\ngit log -g --all --since=\"2 weeks ago\"\ngit log -g --all -S\"some text\"\n```\n\nFor commits no branch/tag/reflog points to, ask Git’s object database:\n\n```bash\ngit fsck --no-reflogs --unreachable --no-progress\n```\n\nList unreachable commits by date:\n\n```bash\ngit fsck --no-reflogs --unreachable --no-progress 2>/dev/null |\n  awk '/unreachable commit/ {print $3}' |\n  while read c; do git show -s --format='%cI %H %s' \"$c\"; done |\n  sort\n```\n\nSearch their patches for content:\n\n```bash\ngit fsck --no-reflogs --unreachable --no-progress 2>/dev/null |\n  awk '/unreachable commit/ {print $3}' |\n  while read c; do\n    git show --format= --patch \"$c\" | grep -qF \"some text\" &&\n      git show -s --format='%cI %H %s' \"$c\"\n  done\n```\n\nImportant bit: unreachable commits are temporary-ish. `git gc` can eventually prune them, so if you find the one you want, immediately rescue it:\n\n```bash\ngit branch rescued-commit <sha>\n```","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-15T18:32:38.767Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}